==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[amanda]]'', feminine form of ''[[amandus]]'', gerund of ''[[amare]]'' (''to [[love]]'') : thus meaning "worthy of being loved" or "worthy of love".

===Proper noun===
'''Amanda'''
# A female [[given name]].

